race.comment: ANTHROPOLOGY (6) is a mare by Shamus Award out of Gimlet on debut. Placed in a recent trial and looks all set for a bright start to her career. RED ENVELOPE (10) is a three-start maiden who resumed from a spell last start and was beaten 2.75 lengths when fourth over 1100m at this track. Among the leading chances with that run under her belt. MARIKO (1) missed the placings two runs back then didn't feature last start when 8 lengths away in sixth over 1050m at Rockhampton after being prominent at the bend. Likely improver with strong prospects. LADY DE VEGA (8) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when half a length away in second over 1100m at this circuit. Presents some value at odds.
